# EMPATHY Architecture Gate (Pro 2.0)

- EMPATHY Pro 2.0 must follow **`CONSTITUTION.md`**, **`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`**, **`docs/ATHLETE_MEMORY_AND_COACH_SCOPE.md`**, **`docs/INGEST_DEVICE_AND_LAB_MATRIX.md`**, and **`docs/TECHNICAL_BLUEPRINT.md`** (use what exists in this repo). **V1 alignment:** where domains match, principles in `nextjs-empathy-pro/ARCHITECTURE_RULES.md` and `nextjs-empathy-pro/SYSTEM_CONTEXT.md` apply; do not introduce patterns V1 explicitly forbids (parallel generative paths, provider-as-source-of-truth for core structure).
- If a user request, proposed refactor, API integration, data model, or UI shortcut would violate that architecture, stop immediately.
- Do not implement the violating request "just for now", as a temporary workaround, or behind parallel paths.
- Instead, explicitly warn that the request conflicts with EMPATHY architecture and explain which rule it breaks.
- Ask for confirmation before any change that touches canonical generation flow, builder centrality, digital athlete model consistency, deterministic engines, protected core modules, or architecture-wide contracts.
- Reject parallel generation logic, duplicate data flows, duplicate provider stacks, and module-local shortcuts when a canonical EMPATHY path already exists.
- Never choose an external provider as the conceptual base of EMPATHY when the provider only covers a narrow subset of the domain.
- Builder remains the canonical single-session generator; downstream modules must consume builder-compatible structured outputs.
- External APIs may enrich or import data, but they must not redefine EMPATHY's core structure.
